      • getMock

        public static final <T> T getMock​(String mockName,
                                  Class<T> className)
                           throws IOException
        To use this method you have to create a folder named "mocks" under the src/main/resources or src/test/resources folder of your project, depending on the application context. In this folder you have to add all the json files you need to mock the objects. To select a mock, you only have to pass to the method the name of the file, without path or extension.
        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        mockName - a String that represents the name of the file in which you are mocking the object
        className - the class of the object you need to mock
        Returns:
        the mocked object
        Throws:
        IOException

      • getMock

        public static final <T> T getMock​(String mockName,
                                  String subfolderPath,
                                  Class<T> className)
                           throws IOException
        To use this method you have to create a folder named "mocks" under the src/main/resources or src/test/resources folder of your project, depending on the application context. In this folder you have to add all the json files you need to mock the objects. To select a mock, you only have to pass to the method the name of the file, without path or extension. This method allow you to specify a different path for the subfolders you want to insert under the root mocks/.
        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        mockName - a String that represents the name of the file in which you are mocking the object
        subfolderPath - a string that represents the subfolder path of root mock-files (mocks/)
        className - the class of the object you need to mock
        Returns:
        the mocked object
        Throws:
        IOException
